  "text": "**Methodology**: Searched all three repos (kubernetes, grafana, etcd) via Sourcegraph keyword/NLS search and local grep for `status.Errorf(codes.`, `status.Error(codes.`, `togRPCError`, `HTTPStatusFromCode`, and gRPC-to-HTTP translation patterns.\n\n**Kubernetes/kubernetes**: gRPC status errors are created at the CRI streaming layer (`staging/src/k8s.io/kubelet/pkg/cri/streaming/server.go` with `codes.InvalidArgument`) and in CSI volume operations. The `cri-api/pkg/errors/errors.go` file provides `IsNotFound()` to check gRPC `codes.NotFound`. The vendored `containerd/errdefs/grpc.go` has bidirectional `ToGRPC`/`FromGRPC` mapping between containerd domain errors and gRPC codes. `pkg/volume/csi/csi_client.go:isFinalError` interprets gRPC status codes (Canceled, DeadlineExceeded, Unavailable, ResourceExhausted, Aborted) to decide retry logic. Kubernetes uses the vendored etcd gRPC gateway (`rpc.pb.gw.go`) for etcd HTTP API translation. There is no centralized Kubernetes-native gRPC-to-HTTP error translation \u2014 instead, the apiserver works primarily with HTTP/REST.\n\n**etcd-io/etcd**: Has the most structured gRPC error system. `api/v3rpc/rpctypes/error.go` defines ~40 pre-declared gRPC status errors (ErrGRPCEmptyKey, ErrGRPCKeyNotFound, etc.) with specific codes. `server/etcdserver/api/v3rpc/util.go` has a `togRPCError()` function with a `toGRPCErrorMap` that translates internal server errors to these gRPC errors. The gRPC-to-HTTP translation uses grpc-gateway: `server/embed/serve.go:registerGateway()` sets up `gw.ServeMux` that routes HTTP `/v3/` requests to gRPC endpoints via `api/etcdserverpb/gw/rpc.pb.gw.go`. The `client/v3/retry_interceptor.go` handles gRPC error codes for retry logic.\n\n**grafana/grafana**: Creates gRPC status errors in authz services (`zanzana/server/auth.go` with `codes.Unauthenticated/PermissionDenied`, `rbac/service.go` with `codes.NotFound/Internal/InvalidArgument`). The gRPC-to-HTTP translation happens in `pkg/storage/unified/resource/errors.go` using `runtime.HTTPStatusFromCode(st.Code())`, in `pkg/tsdb/influxdb/fsql/fsql.go` which manually maps gRPC codes to HTTP status, and in `pkg/services/authz/zanzana/server/openfga_server.go` which configures grpc-gateway error handlers via `ConvertToEncodedErrorCode`. The `pkg/plugins/instrumentationutils/request_status.go` and `pkg/plugins/manager/client/client.go` check `grpcstatus.FromError` for cancellation detection.",
